I'm logged in as "awesomejt" which is a different user that I'm managing.

5
00:00:17.866 --> 00:00:23.100
Logged in as "awesomejt", I want to add "jasongtaylor" as a contributor

6
00:00:23.100 --> 00:00:26.900
to one of my repositories that I have within my user's space.

7
00:00:26.900 --> 00:00:30.966
This feature is specifically for individual users in GitHub

8
00:00:30.966 --> 00:00:35.600
that want to allow different users to contribute to a Git repository directly,

9
00:00:35.600 --> 00:00:39.666
that is grant read and write access to those repositories.

10
00:00:39.666 --> 00:00:44.500
So, I'm going to go down to my repositories logged in as the "awesomejt" user,

11
00:00:44.500 --> 00:00:48.533
and select test, which is just a public repo that I have

12
00:00:48.533 --> 00:00:53.466
as part of my "awesomejt" user. Then I'm going to go down to the right hand side,

13
00:00:53.466 --> 00:00:57.300
of my repository, and I should have my repository menu,

14
00:00:57.300 --> 00:01:00.900
with one of the items being settings. Click on "Settings",

15
00:01:00.900 --> 00:01:04.800
and then on the left hand side is the list of settings options,

16
00:01:04.800 --> 00:01:08.733
one of which is collaborators. Click on "Collaborators",

17
00:01:08.733 --> 00:01:11.900
which then you will land on the collaborators page.

18
00:01:11.900 --> 00:01:17.666
To add a collaborator, just search by their username, or their name, or their email address.

19
00:01:17.666 --> 00:01:23.133
I happen to know the username is "jasongtaylor", which comes up in the search results.

20
00:01:23.133 --> 00:01:27.800
